# Oracle APEX PDF.js Viewer (Amazon S3)

A lightweight PDF viewer for Oracle APEX using **PDF.js** and **Amazon S3 pre-signed URLs**. This solution renders PDFs directly inside an APEX page without requiring the browser's native PDF viewer, making it compatible with desktop and mobile browsers.

## Features

- 📄 Render PDFs directly in Oracle APEX
- ☁️ Supports Amazon S3 pre-signed URLs
- 🔍 Zoom in/out (10%–250%)
- 📱 Mobile-friendly
- ⚡ Uses the latest PDF.js from jsDelivr CDN
- 🎨 Integrates with Oracle APEX Universal Theme
- 🖥 High DPI rendering for Retina displays

---

# Prerequisites

- Oracle APEX 24.x (or later)
- Amazon S3 bucket containing PDF files
- S3 bucket configured with CORS
- PDF URL available in an APEX item

Example:

```sql
P120_ATTACHMENT_ID
```

The item should contain a valid S3 pre-signed URL.

---

# S3 CORS Configuration

Your S3 bucket **must** allow requests from your APEX application.

Example:

```json
[
  {
    "AllowedHeaders": ["*"],
    "AllowedMethods": ["GET","HEAD"],
    "AllowedOrigins": [
      "https://your-apex-domain.com"
    ],
    "ExposeHeaders": []
  }
]
```

Replace:

```
https://your-apex-domain.com
```

with your APEX application URL.

